The gnu-utf8 package contains the GNU gettext toolkit, which is a library for translating string messages into different languages. The App Dependencies issue in gnu-utf8.tar is that it depends on a number of other packages, some of which may have vulnerabilities. This can make the nginx web server vulnerable to attack.

To fix this issue, you can upgrade the gnu-utf8 package to the latest version. This will include the latest security patches and will reduce the number of dependencies that the package has. You can also try to remove any unnecessary dependencies from the package.

This issue belongs to the OWASP Top 10 Web 2021 category **A6: Insecure Deserialization**. This is because the gnu-utf8 package serializes and deserializes data, which can be exploited by an attacker to inject malicious code into the nginx web server.

